    <h1 style="text-align: center;">COVID-19</h1>
    <h2>Information about COVID-19</h2>
    <p style="font-size: larger;"><b>COVID-19 disease is a contagious disease caused by severe acute respiratory syndrome corona virus 2(SARS-CoV-2). It is a transmissible virus and is spreading from one person to the other.The first case was identified in Wuhan,China.The disease is spreading a lot and has led to an ongoing pandemic of COVID-19 Virus.The cases of this disease are rising rapidly as almost all humans are not capable of handling such a strong virus. The first wave of COVID-19 was very impactful in the uprising of health issues in the whole world.It is often termed as the World War 3 because of it's sigificant impact on humans all around the globe.The 2nd COVID wave is the current wave ongoing which is leading to a more bigger number of cases because this time it is much more harmful for children too which was not the case during the 1st wave.This virus has led to a lot number of lockdowns in the whole world which saved a small number of people from getting affected by this. As it's been more than a year of this pandemic in India, the vaccines have been successfully made which is not a complete solution to this problem but a small decline point of COVID-19 cases. </b> </p>

    <a href="https://covid19.who.int/table">Live COVID-19 Cases Tracker</a>

    <h2>Symptopms of this disease include:</h2>
        

Most common symptoms:<ul>
<li>fever</li>
<li>dry cough</li>
<li>tiredness</li></ul>
Less common symptoms:
<ul>
<li>aches and pains</li>
<li>sore throat</li>
<li>diarrhoea</li>
<li>conjunctivitis</li>
<li>headache</li>
<li>loss of taste or smell</li>
<li>a rash on skin, or discolouration of fingers or toes</li></ul>
Serious symptoms:<ul>
<li>difficulty breathing or shortness of breath</li>
<li>chest pain or pressure</li>
<li>loss of speech or movement</li></ul>

    </p>
    <h2>Prevention from Corona Virus</h2>
    <p>To prevent the spread of COVID-19:<ol>
        <li>Clean your hands often. Use soap and water, or an alcohol-based hand rub.</li>
        <li>Maintain a safe distance from anyone who is coughing or sneezing.</li>
        <li>Wear a mask when physical distancing is not possible.</li>
        <li>Don’t touch your eyes, nose or mouth.</li>
        <li>Cover your nose and mouth with your bent elbow or a tissue when you cough or sneeze.</li>
        <li>Stay home if you feel unwell.</li>
        <li>If you have a fever, cough and difficulty breathing, seek medical attention.</li></ol>
        </p>
