<h2>Vaccination Information in India</h2>
<p>A COVID‑19 vaccine is a vaccine intended to provide acquired immunity against severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2 (SARS‑CoV‑2), the virus causing coronavirus disease 2019 (COVID‑19). Two vaccines that have been granted emergency use authorization by the Central Drugs Standard Control Organization (CDSCO) in India are Covishield® (AstraZeneca's vaccine manufactured by Serum Institute of India) and Covaxin® (manufactured by Bharat Biotech Limited).</p>

<p> The procedure to register for the COVID Vaccine is:<ol>
<li>Download the Aarogya Setu app on your mobile phone for Android or iOS.
<a href="https://apps.apple.com/in/app/aarogyasetu/id1505825357">iOS Download</a>
For Android-<a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=nic.goi.aarogyasetu&hl=en_IN&gl=US">Android Download</a>
<li> See if it correctly displays your Covid status.</li>
<li> On the Aarogya Setu app homepage, go to the 'CoWIN' tab.</li>
<li>Under the CoWIN icon, you can see four options - Vaccine Information, Vaccination, Vaccination Certificate, Vaccination Dashboard. Tap on the "Vaccination" tab and then select the "Register Now" option.</li>
<li>Put your mobile number and then click on "proceed to verify".</li>
<li>Enter the OTP and again select "proceed to verify".</li>
</ol>
</p>

